{"title_page": "Fangcang Hospital", "text_new": "{{Infobox hospital\n| name                  = Fangcang Hospital\n| org/group             = \n| logo                  = \n| logo_size             = \n| image                 = \n| image_size            = 225 \n| alt                   = \n| caption               = \n| coordinates           = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline, title}} -->\n| location              = \n| region                = \n| state                 = \n| country               = [[China]]\n| healthcare            = <!-- UK: NHS; AU/CA: Medicare; ELSE free-form text, e.g. Private -->\n| funding               = \n| type                  = Makeshift [[hospital]]\n| religious_affiliation = \n| affiliation           = \n| patron                = \n| network               = \n| standards             = \n| emergency             = \n| beds                  = \n| speciality            = \n| helipad               = \n| h1-number             = \n| h1-length-f           = \n| h1-length-m           = \n| h1-surface            = <!-- up to h12 -->\n| publictransit         = \n| former-names          = \n| constructed           =\n| opened                = <!-- cite in article as well -->\n| closed                = \n| demolished            = \n| website               = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n| other_links           = \n| module                = \n}}\n\n'''Fangcang Hospital''' ({{Lang-zh|c=|s=\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662|t=\u65b9\u8259\u91ab\u9662|p=f\u0101ngc\u0101ng y\u012byu\u00e0n}})<ref>{{YouTube|Wuhan Vlog: A look into a mobile cabin hospital}}</ref> refers to a kind of makeshift hospitals used in the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], most notably in Wuhan. Such hospitals were intended for large-scale medical isolation and instituted through the acquisition of existing space, some even large-scale event venues and renovated colleges and universities.\n\nIn Wuhan, since the outbreak of the [[coronavirus disease 2019]], the general medical institutions and the newly-expanded pneumonia specialist hospital became overcrowded with just severely ill patients. Meanwhile, persons under voluntary family isolation could still infect family members and neighboring community members, impacting the use of medical resources and increasing the risk to epidemic control. Under such circumstances, the principle of centralised treatment of patients with mild symptoms was adopted for the control of infectious diseases. The [[Government of the People's Republic of China]] established 16 square-cabin hospitals in [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], providing a total of more than 20,000 beds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/2020-02/19/c_1125596243.htm|title=\u6b66\u6c49\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u589e\u81f312\u5bb6 \u8ba1\u5212\u542f\u7528\u5e8a\u4f4d\u8d85\u4e24\u4e07\u5f20-\u65b0\u534e\u7f51|website=www.xinhuanet.com|access-date=2020-02-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Yu|first=Verna|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/feb/18/senior-wuhan-doctor-dies-from-coronavirus-as-authorities-start-to-round-up-patients|title=Senior Wuhan doctor dies from coronavirus as authorities start to 'round up' patients|date=2020-02-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/coronavirus-wuhan-to-activate-one-more-temporary-hospital-with-3690-beds|title=Coronavirus: Wuhan to build 19 more makeshift hospitals as China struggles to contain epidemic|last=hermesauto|date=2020-02-21|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> As of March 10, 2020, all patients admitted to the square cabin hospital of Wuhan Wushan Hongshan Stadium were discharged. Thus, all 16 square cabin hospitals in Wuhan completed their missions and their cabins were shut down.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-52016139|title=Wuhan to ease lockdown as world battles virus|date=2020-03-24|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n== Etymology ==\n''Fangcang'' ({{Lang-zh|c=|s=\u65b9\u8231|t=\u65b9\u8259|p=f\u0101ngc\u0101ng}}), lit. \"square cabin\", is a Chinese term referring to a movable modular building structure formed using a combination of various solid materials. Outside of the context of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|outbreak]], \"Fangcang hospital\" usually refers to a kind of modular hospitals quickly built in the form of such ''fangcangs.''\n\n== Locations in Wuhan ==\n[[File:Fangcang Hospitals, Huoshenshan Hospital and Leishenshan Hospital in Wuhan.svg|thumb|The sixteen Fangcang Hospitals in Wuhan]]\nThe following Fangcang hospitals were in use in [[Wuhan]], [[China]] during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]:\n\n* [[Wuhan International Expo Center|Wuhan International Conference & Exhibition Center]], [[Jianghan District]]\n* Wuhan Keting, [[Dongxihu District]]\n* [[Hongshan Stadium]], [[Wuchang District]]\n* [[Wuhan National Fitness Center]], [[Jiang'an District]]\n* [[Wuhan International Expo Center]], [[Hanyang District]]\n* [[Wuhan Stadium]], [[Qiaokou District]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.ifeng.com/c/7uUNaVxyW8W|title=\u6b66\u6c49\u9996\u5bb6\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u201c\u4f11\u8231\u201d \u5eb7\u590d\u8005\u5747\u5df2\u51fa\u9662|website=news.ifeng.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n* [[Wuhan Sports Center]], [[Wuhan Development Zone]]\n* Dahua Mountain, [[Jiangxia District]]\n* [[Optics Valley Convention & Exhibition Center]], Donghu Development Zone\n* Huangpi Sports Center\n* Zhiyingu, [[Caidian District]]\n* Wugang Sports Center, [[Qingshan District, Wuhan|Qingshan District]]\n* Hongqiao Group Industrial Park, Chenjiaji Avenue<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://new.qq.com/omn/20200218/20200218A0B9MQ00.html|title=\u6b66\u6c49\u8c0c\u5bb6\u77f6\u201c\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u201d\u5373\u5c06\u5b8c\u5de5 \u65b0\u6dfb3840\u5f20\u5e8a\u4f4d_\u817e\u8baf\u65b0\u95fb|website=new.qq.com|access-date=2020-02-20}}</ref>\n\n== Outside Mainland China ==\nThe first comparable makeshift hospital in [[Russia]] during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|outbreak]] was built in [[Moscow]] in March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.yicai.com/news/100548424.html|title=\u4fc4\u7f57\u65af\u4e5f\u5f00\u59cb\u5728\u83ab\u65af\u79d1\u5efa\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u4e86|website=m.yicai.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> Makeshift hospitals were successively built in countries including [[Iran]], [[Spain]], [[United Kingdom]], and the [[United States]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://app.cctv.com/special/cportal/detail/arti/index.html?id=ArtiNStwqOxn6G7lkbMzHaTB200322&fromapp=cctvnews&version=727|title=\u5b66\u4e60\u4e2d\u56fd\u7ecf\u9a8c\uff01\u603b\u53f0\u8bb0\u8005\u72ec\u5bb6\u63a2\u8bbf\u4f0a\u6717\u7248\u201c\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u201d|last=|first=|date=|website=app.cctv.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/world-51993469|title=\u80ba\u708e\u75ab\u60c5\u5168\u7403\u786e\u8bca30\u4e07 \u897f\u73ed\u7259\u5f00\u8bbe\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662|date=2020-03-22|work=BBC News \u4e2d\u6587|access-date=2020-03-30|language=zh-Hans}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yicai.com/news/100563956.html|title=\u82f1\u56fd\u7248\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u51c6\u5907\u5efa\u8bbe|website=www.yicai.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjd.com.cn/a/202003/24/WS5e79b89ee4b03cc9592da4f1.html|title=\u4ece\u7ebd\u7ea6\u5230\u5fb7\u9ed1\u5170\uff0c\u5168\u7403\u591a\u5730\u5efa\u8d77\u201c\u65b9\u8231\u533b\u9662\u201d|website=www.bjd.com.cn|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n{{coord missing|China}}\n\n[[Category:2020 establishments in China]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in China]]\n[[Category:Hospitals established for the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox hospital\n| name                  = Fangcang Hos